  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "Butter six 1-cup ramekins and coat with crushed double rise bread.",
    "Roast poblano peppers in the oven until charred, then peel and chop.",
    "In a blender, puree roasted poblanos, eggs, heavy cream, shredded cheese, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Stir in flaked cod fish and toasted chopped pecans.",
    "Pour the mixture into the prepared ramekins and bake for 35 minutes.",
    "Remove from oven and let cool to room temperature.",
    "Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.",
    "Serve chilled and garnished with additional toasted pecans if desired."
  ],
